    "causal_summary": "The per-folder description generator writes non-idempotently. generatePerFolderDescription stamps lastUpdated with new Date and savePerFolderDescription writes unconditionally, so a rerun on unchanged content dirties the folder. Running that generator also triggers ensureDescriptionCache to regenerate the whole tree by scanning every base path, pulling unrelated sessions folders into a scoped commit. The phase adds a content fingerprint over the canonical fields with a per-folder no-op skip, content-gates the aggregate-cache write, and adds a targeted upsertDescriptionCacheEntry that replaces only the changed entry and reserves the full rebuild for structural changes. Both fixes ship behind a default-OFF flag with a grandfather report mode because the existing files carry the wall-clock stamps the gate rejects.",
